Suspected bandits have killed a Deeper Life Bible Churchâ€™s pastor and three other residents of Guma Local Government Area of Benue State. Daily Post reports that the incident which occurred on Tuesday morning triggered tension in most parts of the local government which has been under attack recently. It was gathered that the pastor was killed around Waku village on his way to Gbajimba, the headquarters of Guma LGA for a church activity on Tuesday morning. According to a resident, Mr. Aondoka the other three victims were hacked to death while they were working on their farms in Nyiev council ward. Chairman of Guma LGA, Caleb Aba, confirmed the incident to journalists on Wednesday. Meanwhile, the Benue State Police Command is yet to confirm the incident.